Head capsule parallel-sided, not narrowing anteriad towards bases of mandibles, with four weakly visible white stemmata on each side, without dark pigment spots inside them; frayed setae present from metathorax to apex of abdomen; apotome with short stalk not extending beyond tentorial pits (
Fig. 6B
); inner margin of mandible without small tooth (
Fig. 6A, E
); maxillary and labial palp 3- and 2-segmented, respectively, last segment of maxillary palp longer than penultimate segment, weakly divided into two pseudosegments (
Fig. 6E
); protibial comb with irregular row of 8–10 split (bifid) spines (
Fig. 7C
).

